{"id":"combustion-flame-8","label":"Combustion and Flame","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"mcq","label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions"},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Which one of the following gases is used in combustion?","options":"Oxygen, Hydrogen, Nitrogen, Carbon dioxide"},{"qText":"The burning of LPG is an example of","options":"rapid combustion, spontaneous combustion, slow combustion, explosion"},{"qText":"A temperature at which the substance burns is called ","options":"ignition temperature, melting point, boiling temperature, evaporation"},{"qText":"Which is non-renewable source of energy?","options":"Natural gas, Wind energy, Tidal energy, Mechanical energy"},{"qText":"Which of the following is not a fossil fuel?","options":"Water gas, Coal, Petroleum, Natural gas"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which gas helps in the process of combustion?","options":"Oxygen gas, Cooking gas, Nitrogen gas, Producer gas"},{"qText":"The amount of heat energy produced on complete combustion of 1 kg of a fuel is called","options":"calorific value, significant value, heat value, internal energy"},{"qText":"Which zone represents the partial combustion in candle flame?","options":"Middle zone, Outer zone, Inner zone, Lower zone"},{"qText":"Burning coal in a closed room will produce","options":"carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, nitrogen oxides, oxygen"},{"qText":"Substances which catch fire are called","options":"combustible, acids, bases, burners"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Out of these, which is able to control fires?","options":"CO2, NH3, H2, F2"},{"qText":"Which zone of a flame does a goldsmith use for melting gold and silver ?","options":"Outer zone, Middle zone, Inner zone, Lower zone"},{"qText":"Calorific value of a fuel is expressed in","options":"kilojoule per kilogram, kilojoule per gram, joule per milligram, kilojoule per milligram"},{"qText":"Which of the following is a non-combustible substance?","options":"Iron nails, Wood, Paper, Straw"},{"qText":"Acid rain contains mainly","options":"nitrogen oxide and sulphur dioxide, oxygen and nitrogen gas, fluorine and chlorine gas, magnesium oxide"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Heat and light produced in the sun is by:","options":"nuclear reactions, combustion, burning"},{"qText":"Which of the following gas extinguishes fire?","options":"carbon dioxide, hydrogen, oxygen, nitrogen"},{"qText":"Combustion that takes place at a very fast rate is called:","options":"rapid combustion, explosion,  spontaneous combustion"},{"qText":"Which one of the following is combustible?","options":"Paper, Iron nail, Stone pieces, Glass"},{"qText":"Which one of the following is fuel of our body?","options":"Food, Water, Petrol, Diesel"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"The lowest temperature at which a substance catches fire is called its","options":"Ignition temperature, Critical temperature, Boiling point, Melting point"},{"qText":"Essential requirements for producing fire are:","options":"Heat, Fuel, Air, * All of these"},{"qText":"Rapid combustion is","options":"When gas burns, it produces heat and light\n              When material suddenly burst into flames\n              When there is evolution of heat"},{"qText":"When magnesium ribbon burns it produce","options":"Magnesium oxide, Magnesium sulphate, Magnesium hydroxide, Magnesium chloride"},{"qText":"Coal burns with ______","options":"Only glow\n              Only Flame\n              Flame and glow"}]}]}]}